occupation: Lawyer;Burgess and High Sheriff;Member of Virginia House of Burgesses
bio: Benjamin Harrison IV was an American Virginia planter, politician, and member of the Virginia House of Burgesses.

occupation: Member of the Virginia House of Burgesses;Signer of the Declaration of Independence
bio: Benjamin Harrison V was an American planter and merchant, a revolutionary leader, and a Founding Father of the United States.
Elizabeth Bassett Harrison was the wife of Benjamin Harrison V and the mother of William Henry Harrison, the ninth President of the United States.
William Henry Harrison was an American military officer and politician who served as the ninth president of the United States.
Dilsia was a slave who had a son, Oliver, with William Henry Harrison.
Oliver Harrison was the son of Dilsia and William Henry Harrison.
Margaret Wills was the spouse of Oliver Harrison and the mother of Mary Ann Harrison.
Mary Ann Harrison was the daughter of Oliver Harrison and Margaret Wills.
